# ToastMessage

Toast Messages inform customers that a task was successful. These messages provide customers with immediate feedback upon completing an action.
Toast Messages are time-limited and will disappear automatically, even if customers take no further action.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/toast-message
```

```tsx
import { ToastMessage } from '@ids-ts/toast-message';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `actionLabel` | `string` | Yes | - |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Id used for automation testing |
| `dismissible` | `boolean` | Yes | - |
| `duration` | `number` | Yes | - |
| `icon` | `React.ReactElement` | Yes | - |
| `onActionClick` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | Callback for extra functionality when action is clicked |
| `onClose` | `(event?: React.KeyboardEvent) => void` | No | Callback for when toast message is closed |
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | - |
| `showIcon` | `boolean` | Yes | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface ToastMessageProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /**
   * Value to be displayed on button
   *
   * @default 'Close'
   */
  actionLabel: string;
  /** Id used for automation testing */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * Bool to show cross button or not
   *
   * @default true
   */
  dismissible: boolean;
  /**
   * Set the time period for Toast Message to be visible
   *
   * @default 6000
   */
  duration: number;
  /**
   * icon component
   *
   * @default <CircleCheckFill focusable="false" data-testid="circleCheckIcon" />
   */
  icon: React.ReactElement;
  /** Callback for extra functionality when action is clicked */
  onActionClick?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /** Callback for when toast message is closed */
  onClose?: (event?: React.KeyboardEvent) => void;
  /**
   * Whether to show the toast message
   *
   * @default false
   */
  open: boolean;
  /**
   * Bool to show an icon or not
   *
   * @default false
   */
  showIcon: boolean;
}
```

</details>

